# Hecate Core Rules

This is the Cursor adapter for Hecate agent guidance.

The canonical, provider-neutral instruction layer for this repo lives in
[`docs-ai/`](../../docs-ai/README.md). Start there and load the relevant skill
from [`docs-ai/skills/`](../../docs-ai/skills/).

This adapter must stay thin: do not copy architecture rules, verification
ladders, planning triggers, review rubrics, or skill content into `.cursor`.
Update `docs-ai/` first, then update this adapter only when Cursor discovery
needs to change.

## Pointers

- Entry point: [`docs-ai/README.md`](../../docs-ai/README.md).
- Adapter policy: [`docs-ai/core/agent-guidance.md`](../../docs-ai/core/agent-guidance.md).
- Project context: [`docs-ai/core/project-context.md`](../../docs-ai/core/project-context.md).
- Workflow: [`docs-ai/core/workflow.md`](../../docs-ai/core/workflow.md).
- Verification: [`docs-ai/core/verification.md`](../../docs-ai/core/verification.md).
